Preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce. Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and dice half the @yellow onion{1}(peeled and diced half) into ½-inch pieces (use the rest as you like). Core, deseed, and dice @long green pepper{1}(cored, deseeded, and diced into ½-inch pieces). Mince @cilantro{¼%ounce}(minced).

Toss potatoes, diced onion, and green pepper on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, @fry seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Spread out across entire sheet. Roast on top rack until veggies are golden brown, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, place @bacon{4%ounce} in a dry #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Cook, turning occasionally, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer bacon to a #paper towel-lined plate{}. Discard all but a thin layer of bacon fat (you'll use it to cook the eggs).

> TIP: Lower heat if bacon begins to brown too quickly.

Return pan with bacon fat to medium heat. Once hot, crack @eggs{2} into pan and cover. Fry eggs to preference. Season with salt and pepper. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Once veggies have 3-5 minutes left, remove from oven. Halve @potato buns{2} and place cut sides up on same baking sheet. Sprinkle top buns with @Monterey Jack cheese{½%cup}. Return to oven until bread is toasted, cheese melts, and veggies are tender.

Spread cut sides of bottom buns with a bit of @ketchup{4%tablespoon}; fill buns with bacon and eggs. Toss veggies with cilantro. Divide veggies and sandwiches between plates. Serve with remaining ketchup on the side.